Given what I found when I investigated bug 151300, and given that this does not fail when NOT using the language packs, I'm going to go out on a limb and assume that the same problem there is impacting here. SetConfig.java line#932 is			logging = doc.createElement(Logging.TAG);
Logging.java line#17 says
	public final static String TAG = ConfigUtility.getString("Config.Logging.Tag");
SetConfig.properties line#66 says
Config.Logging.Tag=Logging

Note that this is between the "Stop translating" and "Start translating" lines... there's not bad characters here that I see. They must have been introduced by (inappropriate) translation!
